3:
The wicked go astray even when they are in the womb;
\q they go astray from birth, speaking lies.
\q

4:
Their poison is like a snake's poison;
\q they are like a deaf adder that stops up its ears,
\q

6:
Break their teeth in their mouths, God;
\q break out the great teeth of the young lions, Yahweh.
\q

7:
Let them melt away as water that runs off;
\q when they shoot their arrows, let them be as though they had no points.
\q

10:
The righteous will rejoice when he sees God's vengeance;
\q he will wash his feet in the blood of the wicked,
\q
